document_data.Possessions:
Zehira wore a suit of [[mariner's studded leather]] armor, decorated with a motif featuring aquatic sea life. This armor allowed her to swim much more effectively than most.{{Cite adventurers league/Uncertain Scrutiny|71}}

Among Zehira's personal effects were a golden coin featuring the Deryan family symbol of an [[albatross]], her sketchbook, and a [[gold]] hair pin.

While captive on a lone island, Zehira acquired a [[barnacle]]-covered club that she used as a bludgeoning weapon, and continued wielding it even after joining the Turmish navy. This club was in fact the ''[[Iltkazar Scepter]]'', a dwarven [[artifact]] associated with [[Clangeddin Silverbeard]].

History.Early Adventures:
Some time during the late 15{{th}} century DR, Zehira left her home and joined with a band of privateers to fight against the forces of Thay.{{Cite adventurers league/Breaking Umberlee's Resolve|14}} Zehira's family assumed she ran off to the [[Pirate Isles]] and dispatched [[djinn]] named [[Mezhar]] to bring her back safely to Alaghôn.{{Cite adventurers league/Breaking Umberlee's Resolve|7}} In truth, her vessel was attacked by the pirates and Zehira was taken captive aboard ''[[Umberlee's Resolve]]''.{{Cite adventurers league/Breaking Umberlee's Resolve|4}} The ship subsequently ran aground on [[Hawk's Isle]],{{Cite adventurers league/Breaking Umberlee's Resolve|8}} and Zehira was taken captive by a [[morkoth]] called [[Axar Xyrl]]. After suffering these ordeals, Zehira was eventually rescued by a band of adventurers that were employed by Mezhar.{{Cite adventurers league/Breaking Umberlee's Resolve|14}}

Upon returning home, Zehira officially joined the privateers of Turmish as a captain,{{Cite adventurers league/Blood in the Water|3}} and commissioned ''Umberlee's Resolve'' to be repaired as her own ship.{{Cite adventurers league/Blood in the Water|12}} Zehira and her fellows were framed for the murders by the real culprit, a [[malenti]], a [[sahuagin]] that held the likeness of a sea elf. While the group did not catch the murderous malenti, they managed to clear their name and leave Myth Nantar relatively unharmed.{{Cite adventurers league/Blood in the Water|15-16}}

As Zehira and her allies sailed away from the sea elf city, a Thayan ship led by a [[arcane trickster|spellcaster]] named [[Rune (person)|Rune]] intercepted ''Umberlee's Resolve'', raided the vessel, and once again abducted Zehira. They took her to the Thayan hideaway within the [[Infernal Maw]], a volcano on [[Dragon Isle]], with the goal of recovering a mysterious barnacle-covered club that had come into her possession.{{Cite adventurers league/Saving Silverbeard|5-7}} Zehira's adventuring companions came to her rescue once again, freeing her from the Red Wizards and accompanying her to [[Ayakar]]. They parted ways as friends.{{Cite adventurers league/Saving Silverbeard|10-12}}

History.Search For the Storm King:
Some time later, Zehira's presence was requested at court of King [[Hekaton]], king of the [[storm giant]]s and ruler of [[Maelstrom]]. The Storm King sought to utilize the ''Iltkazar Scepter'' for their own ends. Accompanied by adventurers once again, Zehira arrived at Maelstrom only to discover King Hekaton and the ''[[Wyrmskull Throne]]'' had gone missing.{{Cite adventurers league/Foreign Affairs|3}} The king's daughter, Princess [[Serissa]] implored Zehira and her party to find the whereabouts of King Hekaton and bring back both he and the throne to the storm giant city.{{Cite adventurers league/Foreign Affairs|6-7}}

The search for King Hekaton took Zehira and her group to the [[Mere of Dead Men]] and [[Dragonhorn Manor]] in the city of [[Waterdeep]], where they became aware of [[Cult of the Dragon]]'s involvement in the abduction.{{Cite adventurers league/Foreign Affairs|21}} they continued their search in the [[Thay]]an city of [[Eltabbar]]. The group discovered King Hekaton had been taken to the dungeons of the dark [[Citadel]] in [[Thaymount]], and infiltrated the fortress with the hopes of rescuing him. Unfortunately they were too late; Hekaton had been slain and raised as a [[death knight]] in service to Thay's [[lich]]-king, [[Szass Tam]].{{Cite adventurers league/Uncertain Scrutiny|2}} While Zehira and her allies managed to escape the Citadel with their lives, they could not avoid detection by Szass Tam's powerful magics.{{Cite adventurers league/Uncertain Scrutiny|39-40}}

Turning their focus towards the ''Wyrmskull Throne'', Zehira and her group accompanied the storm giant [[Tellan]] to the [[Shadowed Tower]], in the [[Cloak Wood]] forest of the [[Western Heartlands]], an outpost of the Cult of the Dragon. A hint of specific magic discovered within took them to nearby [[Candlekeep]], where it was revealed an sage named [[Alsbith]] could perform a ritual to locate the throne.{{Cite adventurers league/Thimblerigging|3}} Alsbith did require a specific tome entitled ''[[The Death of the Mind]]'', which could only be found in the [[Tomb of the Nine Gods]] in the far-southern land of [[Chult]].{{Cite adventurers league/Thimblerigging|14}} Zehira and the others recovered the tome for the sage, but encountered agents of Thay in the Chultan tomb.{{Cite adventurers league/Thimblerigging|18-19}} They then retrieved a [[shadow magic]] duplicate of the throne from within [[Wyvernfang]] in the [[Thunder Peaks]], the final piece required for the ritual.{{Cite adventurers league/Moment of Peace|2-3}}

Alsbith's ritual revealed the real ''Wyrmskull Throne'' was in the possession of the [[blue dragon|blue]] [[dracolich]] [[Iymrith]], at her [[Iymrith's tower|tower]] in the [[Plains of Purple Dust]]. Zehira and the adventurers defeated Iymrith―temporarily destroying her corporeal form―and recovered the throne, learning that it had been repurposed as her [[phylactery]].{{Cite adventurers league/Moment of Peace|16}} Unfortunately, while away on that last quest, the raised-as-undead King Hekaton stole the throne and began the journey to bring it to Szass Tam in Thay.{{Cite adventurers league/Wings of  Death|39}} she joined them on the quest to recover his soul from the depths of the Nine Hells.{{Cite adventurers league/The Harrowing of Hell|3}}

History.Defiance of the Red Wizards:
After rallying from the attack, Zehira joined Remallia and the adventurers for a final mission to stop the Red Wizards from harnessing the unstable powers of Xorvintroth.{{Cite adventurers league/Frozen Whispers|5}} They infiltrated the Red Wizard encampments and contacted [[Jaan'vald Llanou]], the leader of a faction of rebellious slaves that sought to overthrow their Thayan oppressors. Together they sabotaged the Red Wizards' operations, granting the slaves an opportunity to escape with their lives.{{Cite adventurers league/Uprising|2-3}} Jaan'vald led the adventures through the city and into the [[Supreme Forge]]. Within, they were able to gather enough Aberian artifacts, and Zehira crafted a ''[[portal disruptor]]'', which when used, could put an end to the Red Wizards' schemes.{{Cite adventurers league/Expedition to the Supreme Forge|2-3}} The adventurers were successful in their mission, and managed to destroy the Thayan-controlled manufactory.{{Cite adventurers league/Against the Machine|2}}

Following their shared success, the allies regrouped to coordinate their next move. An unexpected earthquake made apparent their work was not done ― the excavation had unleashed some power far more dangerous they had encountered previously. Zehira's stalwart adventurer allies explored the depths of Xorvintroth and discovered the [[elder evil]] known as [[Father Llymic]] had opened a series of rifts that let loose [[star spawn]]s and his own [[brood spawn]] upon Toril. They managed to close the portal and prevented Father Llymic from gaining admittance to the Realms.{{Cite adventurers league/Fall the Cold Night|3}}

Finally, Zehira and Remallia regrouped with their ally [[Damita Uthros]], to face one final threat in Xorvintroth: [[Szass Tam]]. The lich king of Thay arrived at Xorvintroth and was ambushed by the forces of Dar'lon Ma, the zulkir of Thay that aided in Zehira's efforts to seek out King Hekaton. Zehira and the adventurers joined together once again to defeat Szass Tam and stopped the Red Wizards' malign plans for the Realms once again.{{Cite adventurers league/The Death of Szass Tam|3-4}}
